question_id,subject,difficulty,question_text,expected_keywords,ideal_answer\n1,OS,Easy,What is a process?,process, A process is a program in execution.\n2,OS,Medium,What is the difference between a process and a thread?,process, A process is an independent program whereas threads are subsets of processes.\n3,DBMS,Easy,What is a database?,database, A database is an organized collection of data.\n4,DBMS,Medium,What is normalization?,normalization, Normalization is the process of organizing data in a database.\n5,DSA,Easy,What is a linked list?,DSA, A linked list is a data structure consisting of nodes that together represent a sequence.\n6,DSA,Medium,What is the time complexity of binary search?,DSA, O(log n)\n7,OS,Hard,Explain multithreading.,multithreading, Multithreading is the concurrent execution of more than one sequential set of instructions.\n8,DBMS,Hard,What are ACID properties?,ACID, ACID properties ensure reliable processing of database transactions.\n9,DSA,Hard,What is a graph?,graph, A graph is a collection of nodes connected by edges.\n10,OS,Easy,Define semaphore.,semaphore, A semaphore is a variable used to control access to a common resource in a concurrent system.\n11,OS,Medium,What is paging?,paging, Paging is a memory management scheme that eliminates the need for contiguous allocation of physical memory.\n12,DBMS,Easy,What is SQL?,SQL, SQL is Structured Query Language used for managing and manipulating databases.\n13,DBMS,Medium,What is a foreign key?,foreign key, A foreign key is a field in one table that refers to the primary key in another table.\n14,DSA,Easy,What is a stack?,stack, A stack is a collection of elements with two principal operations: push and pop.\n15,DSA,Medium,What is the time complexity of insertion in an array?,array, O(n)\n16,OS,Hard,What is deadlock?,deadlock, Deadlock is a state in a multiprocessing environment where two or more processes are unable to proceed because each is waiting for the other to finish.\n17,DBMS,Hard,Explain the difference between clustered and non-clustered indexes.,indexing, Clustered indexes determine the physical order of data in a table whereas non-clustered indexes do not.\n18,DSA,Hard,What is a binary tree?,binary tree, A binary tree is a tree data structure in which each node has at most two children.\n19,OS,Easy,What is a thread?,thread, A thread is the smallest unit of processing that can be scheduled by an operating system.\n20,DBMS,Medium,What is denormalization?,denormalization, Denormalization is the process of trying to optimize the read performance of a database by adding redundant data.\n...\n...\n198,DSA,Medium,What is a Hash Table?,hashing, A hash table stores key-value pairs for efficient data access.\n199,DSA,Hard,What are the advantages of using a linked list over an array?,linked list, Linked lists are dynamic and can grow and shrink in size easily, while arrays have a fixed size.\n200,OS,Hard,Explain the role of the kernel in an operating system.,kernel, The kernel is the core component of an operating system that manages system resources and communication between hardware and software.